go-sqlcipher
============

This repository is a fork of github.com/mutecomm/go-sqlcipher, originally
authored by Frank Braun and contributors between 2017 and 2020. Maintenance
upstream stopped in December 2020 (last commit: 25f68ad, "update modules").
We forked at that commit on 2026-04-29 to resume tracking the SQLCipher
release cadence.

The fork preserves the original git history, license terms, and code
attribution intact. New contributions on top of the original tree are
licensed under the same terms (BSD-3-Clause) for consistency.

The vendored C source files are not original to either fork. They are
shipped under the licenses of their upstream projects, reproduced verbatim
in LICENSE:

  - SQLCipher       — BSD-3-Clause, copyright 2008 ZETETIC LLC
                      https://github.com/sqlcipher/sqlcipher
  - SQLite          — public domain (no copyright asserted)
                      https://sqlite.org
  - libtomcrypt     — public domain (LibTom license)
                      https://github.com/libtom/libtomcrypt
  - mattn/go-sqlite3 — MIT, copyright 2014 Yasuhiro Matsumoto
                      https://github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3

